Our study showed that the incidence of HFRS presented apparent seasonality and that there were two annual peaks in Anqiu City in East China: the smaller peak occurred in spring between April and June, and the larger peak occurred in winter between October and November. Our results support the need to carry out deratization campaigns in spring and winter around the City as well as enhance population immunity by vaccination throughout the year. In addition, we applied a 



